# Install Ruby

Open "Terminal" and type following:

`sudo apt-get install ruby1.9.1-dev`

You will be asked to given the password for root user, please input and press Enter.

![alt text](https://github.com/hy1984427/BDD-with-PageObject/EnvironmentSetup/InstallRuby1.png "Install Ruby")

Then you will see following message in "Terminal", just type y and Enter.

![alt text](https://github.com/hy1984427/BDD-with-PageObject/EnvironmentSetup/InstallRuby2.png "Install Ruby")

Then you should see following screen after install successfully.

![alt text](https://github.com/hy1984427/BDD-with-PageObject/EnvironmentSetup/InstallRuby3.png "Install Ruby")

You can type `ruby -v` to see the ruby version you have installed.

![alt text](https://github.com/hy1984427/BDD-with-PageObject/EnvironmentSetup/InstallRuby4.png "Install Ruby")
